Stevensville School Food Service
June 2 at 8:17 AM ¬∑

The buses will be located at Burnt Fork Market and at the intersection of Airport Rd & Illinois Bench to hand out breakfasts & lunches from 10am until 12pm!

These meals are FREE for all of the children in Stevensville!

Come on down, give us a smile and get some food!

Spread the word!

You may notice some repeat meals as we get closer to the year end.

You may notice what you get at the bus stop isn‚Äôt the exact same as what you get on the bus route.

We are working on getting through some of the items we would like to use before school is out for the summer! So, we are packing the same or similar meals a couple of days in a row.

Thank you for your understanding!

Look forward to seeing you all tomorrow!

shared_text:
Stevi High
May 11 at 2:12 PM ¬∑

Here is the checkout schedule for our students, in grades 9-11. We will have all students grades 9-11 checkout, return chrome books, and clean out lockers in the first week of June.

Here is the schedule for the last week of school.

June 2nd-all 11 grade students will come into the building for checkout.

June 3rd-all 10th grade students will come in for checkout.

June 4th-all 9th grade students will come in for checkout.

Students will be allowed into the building, 15 students at a time to checkout and pick up items in their locker.

Also-May 22nd will be the last day for all new assignments for students in grades 9-11. This will leave the last week of May (26-29th) to turn in all final assignments for credit. The last day to accept student work will be on May 29th.

Thanks,

Principal Gum

Senior Parents,

Thank you for your feedback in regards to the graduation situation. After looking through the responses, it‚Äôs clear that our parents and students would like to have graduation on May 30th, at the SHS gymnasium. We will navigate all the construction as it happens and plan accordingly.

The post and survey was an opportunity for you to voice your opinion about a very important ceremony. The school was placed in a difficult position, to have to make decisions based on the most recent construction timelines. Our job at SHS is to give your child, the best experience possible when it comes to this ceremony. This was the purpose behind the survey.

Sincerely,

Principal Gum
